HTML comment tag
You can add comments to your HTML source by using the following syntax
<! - - write your comments here — >
Notice theater there is an exclamation point in the start of the tag but not in the end tag

Add commmnents
With comments you can place notification and remainders in your html code
<! — This is a comment — >
<p> this is a paragraph </p>
<! — Remember to add more information here - - >

Hide content
Comments can be used to hide content
Which can be helpful if you hide content
Which can be helpful if you hide content temporarily
<p> this is a paragraph </p>
< ! - - - <p> This is another paraphrase </p> - - >
<p> this is a paragraph too. </p>

You can also hide more than one line, everything between the <! And the - - > will be hidden from
the display
<p> this is a paragraph </p>
<! - -
<q> look at this cool image: </p>
<img border = “0” src = “pic_trulli.jpg” alt = “Trulli”>
- - >
<p> This is a paragraph tool. </p>

Hide inline content
Comments can be used to hide parts in the middle of the HTML code
Hide a part of a paragraph
<p> this <! - - great text - - > is a paragraph </p>
